article:
These are 'lists of Oregon-related topics', attempting to list every list
related to the state of Oregon.

* If an article name ends in #Oregon (or some other region), it is a section
  within an article about more than Oregon.
* The topic category is useful for comparing similar entries side-by-side.
  Unfortunately, it is a subjective opinion about the article's primary topic.
  Meta indicates the entry is not a Wikipedia encyclopedia article, but a meta-
  page which organizes the writing of articles.
* If the type is list, the article is primarily a list of articles. If type is
  context, each entry contains summary information useful to compare and
  contrast entries.
* Approx. entries was the number of article entries within the article at one
  time. The value can be helpful for determining the relevancy or depth of
  the article.
